# Testing

- Unit tests cover **pure logic only** — `classify` (200-only rule) and stats
  accumulation/serialization. No network calls in unit tests.
- Keep tests deterministic: construct `CheckResult` values directly instead of
  performing real HTTP requests.
- Register every test with ctest so `ctest --test-dir build` runs the full suite.
- Network behavior is verified **manually** against `httpbin.org`
  (e.g. `/status/200`, `/status/404`, `/status/503`), not in automated tests.

```cpp
// GOOD: pure, deterministic — no network
CheckResult r; r.http_status = 503;
assert(classify(r) == Status::Down);
```
